"{\"uid\": \"cityam.com-yee-growth-and-maturity-key-to-paris-2024-triathlon-gold-dream\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 45, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.\", \"from\": 47, \"to\": 92, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.\", \"from\": 94, \"to\": 139, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By:Matt Hardy  Deputy Sports Editor - City AM  Alex Yee stormed into the Team GB spotlight three years ago when he claimed a gold and a silver in the Tokyo 2020 triathlons.\", \"from\": 141, \"to\": 313, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 144, \"end\": 154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Hardy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matt Hardy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Hardy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Hardy\"}, {\"begin\": 188, \"end\": 196, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alex Yee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\"}, {\"begin\": 291, \"end\": 296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9791465932504136, \"rank\": 0.021297309921178075, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a scene of agony in the individual event where, leading into the run, Yee was tracked down and overtaken by Norway's Kristian Blummenfelt.\", \"from\": 315, \"to\": 460, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 430, \"end\": 436, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\", \"score\": 0.9789637730557981, \"rank\": 0.01318470375653766, \"text\": \"Norway\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\"}, {\"begin\": 439, \"end\": 459, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kristian_Blummenfelt\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kristian Blummenfelt\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kristian_Blummenfelt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kristian_Blummenfelt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But days later in the mixed relay the now 26-year-old, alongside Jess Learmonth, Jonathan Brownlee and Georgia Taylor-Brown, won the elusive gold medal.\", \"from\": 462, \"to\": 614, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 527, \"end\": 541, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jess_Learmonth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jess Learmonth\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jess_Learmonth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jess_Learmonth\"}, {\"begin\": 543, \"end\": 560, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonny_Brownlee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jonathan Brownlee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonny_Brownlee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonny_Brownlee\"}, {\"begin\": 565, \"end\": 585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Taylor-Brown\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Georgia Taylor-Brown\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Taylor-Brown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Taylor-Brown\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With nearly 50 per cent of Team GB in Paris competing in their first Olympic Games, Yee is now one of the more experienced ones - albeit not quite having the longevity, yet, of Andy Murray or Helen Glover.\", \"from\": 616, \"to\": 821, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 643, \"end\": 650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999421754654, \"rank\": 5.78245672576659e-08, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 654, \"end\": 659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999963170012, \"rank\": 3.6830906589432015e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 793, \"end\": 804, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3857915207096837e-28, \"text\": \"Andy Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 808, \"end\": 820, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"score\": 0.9968858553497992, \"rank\": 0.0031234382808593376, \"text\": \"Helen Glover\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the Londoner insists he is more mature now than ever before.\", \"from\": 822, \"to\": 886, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do feel like I have matured a lot,\\\" Yee said on Tuesday ahead of the men's individual event on 30 July.\", \"from\": 888, \"to\": 994, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am really excited to show that.\", \"from\": 995, \"to\": 1029, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Stay in the game with The Turnover: your weekly roundup of sport business news, expert analysis and behind\\u2011the\\u2011scenes stories from City\\u202fAM's sports desk.\", \"from\": 1031, \"to\": 1184, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I feel like I am in much more of a position where I am able to dictate what I am doing and the people around me to get the best out of everyone.\", \"from\": 1186, \"to\": 1331, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I feel very prepared.\", \"from\": 1333, \"to\": 1355, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And I am really looking forward to just starting.\\\"\", \"from\": 1356, \"to\": 1406, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The pressure is on Yee and Team GB to perform in the triathlons across this year's Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1408, \"to\": 1505, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1435, \"end\": 1442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999421754654, \"rank\": 5.78245672576659e-08, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Britain has been the best nation at the sport in the last three Olympiads, including Tokyo where the relay was introduced for the first time.\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1648, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1507, \"end\": 1514, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.7693255373255813, \"rank\": 0.2998393699613419, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 1592, \"end\": 1597, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9791465932504136, \"rank\": 0.021297309921178075, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GB did not medal in either the men's or women's events prior to London 2012 but have picked up eight medals out of a possible 21 since then.\", \"from\": 1650, \"to\": 1795, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1650, \"end\": 1657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999421754654, \"rank\": 5.78245672576659e-08, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 1719, \"end\": 1730, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999953404313, \"rank\": 4.659222912144192e-09, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Twice - thanks to the Brownlees - Britain has achieved double podiums (2012 and 2016).\", \"from\": 1796, \"to\": 1882, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Somebody gave me the advice to put my medal in a sock and then put it in a drawer [after Tokyo].\", \"from\": 1884, \"to\": 1981, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1974, \"end\": 1979, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9791465932504136, \"rank\": 0.021297309921178075, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So that's the first thing I did when I got in the hotel room after the individual [race],\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1982, \"to\": 2081, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have been working with a psychologist and for me I have found a huge power in debriefing what I do, whether that is a success or a failure.\", \"from\": 2083, \"to\": 2225, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A lot of my growth comes from being able to analyse and understand what's happening and actually just kind of put it in a box and move on.\\\"\", \"from\": 2226, \"to\": 2365, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This year Yee and Taylor-Brown will be joined by Kate Waugh, Sam Dickinson and Beth Potter.\", \"from\": 2367, \"to\": 2458, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2416, \"end\": 2420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\", \"score\": 0.9999663591467438, \"rank\": 3.3640370758205824e-05, \"text\": \"Kate\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\"}, {\"begin\": 2428, \"end\": 2441, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Dickinson\", \"score\": 0.999985295493271, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sam Dickinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13415036\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Dickinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Dickinson\"}, {\"begin\": 2446, \"end\": 2457, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beth_Potter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Beth Potter\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beth_Potter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beth_Potter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Potter is the leading female triathlete for Team GB and qualified for the team, along with Yee, in 2023.\", \"from\": 2459, \"to\": 2563, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2503, \"end\": 2510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999421754654, \"rank\": 5.78245672576659e-08, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is the first Games since 2004 without one of the Brownlee brothers in Team GB.\", \"from\": 2564, \"to\": 2645, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2616, \"end\": 2624, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Brownlee\", \"score\": 0.9979682320528771, \"rank\": 0.0016941458258669193, \"text\": \"Brownlee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Brownlee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Brownlee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have got some world leading athletes,\\\" Yee added.\", \"from\": 2647, \"to\": 2700, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I always say we are led by our women.\", \"from\": 2701, \"to\": 2739, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That was shown by how hard that selection was, to get into the team itself  \\\"It's extremely exciting, and to be led by some very strong women is never a bad thing, is it?\", \"from\": 2741, \"to\": 2912, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are going to still have an extremely experienced relay team [without the Brownlees] which will be good.\\\"\", \"from\": 2914, \"to\": 3022, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Share this article  Subscribe to the City AM newsletter to have our top stories delivered directly to your inbox.\", \"from\": 3024, \"to\": 3137, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow us for breaking news and latest updates\", \"from\": 3139, \"to\": 3185, \"entities\": []}]}"